 Jew, Joseph of Arimathea (Matthew 27:57; Mark 15:43; Luke 23:50; John 19:38), who took Jesus down from the Cross, wrapped him in a shroud, and buried him in a rock tomb. According to medieval legend, Joseph of Arimathea brought the Holy Grail to Britain. The name was uncommon in Britain in the Middle Ages but was revived in the mid 16th century and had become popular by the 1630s, remaining so ever since."],"variants":[{"name":"Josef","meanings":[", Dutch, Scandinavian, and Czech spelling of   Joseph  , now also in use in the English‐speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":9,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":11,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":25,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Joseph Felt was born about 1560, in Wiltshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1560–":"umbes 1560–Surnud","1580–1653":"1580–1653","1560–Male":"1560–Surnud","1569":"1569","1653":"1653","1585":"1585","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1580":"1580","about 1560":"umbes 1560","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1560–":"noin 1560–Kuollut","1580–1653":"1580–1653","1560–Male":"1560–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1653":"1653","1585":"1585","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1580":"1580","about 1560":"noin 1560","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1560–":"environ 1